Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.47,0:02:03.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In our art, it is said that incense is heard, rather than smelt.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.98,0:02:12.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seeing, hearing, eating, drinking; there\Nare many pleasures in which men can engage.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.94,0:02:19.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To hear a scent is certainly the most refined of them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.16,0:02:23.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are many styles surrounding the art of incense,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.45,0:02:29.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the Fue-no-Kouji School was\Nthought to have perished long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.71,0:02:34.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It surprised me to hear, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.13,0:02:40.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that the beautiful Lady Ruri was the sole heir\Nto, and only practitioner of, this ancient style.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.80,0:02:46.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I asked her if we might be married,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.89,0:02:54.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for it is my wish to restore the\NFue-no-Kouji School to its former greatness.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.48,0:03:01.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, there were three other candidates, making a\Ntotal of four men, who were vying for Lady Ruri’s hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.70,0:03:05.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Four suitors for a single lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.12,0:03:09.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Ruri was put in quite an uncomfortable position,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.08,0:03:14.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and so, she decided to judge them based on a Kumikou Trial.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.25,0:03:20.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In layman’s terms, she would decide which\Nsuitor to marry based upon a battle of incense, of sorts.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.10,0:03:29.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nakarai-han, I understand you run a commercial fishery,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.77,0:03:32.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but also know much of the art of incense.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.48,0:03:35.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear that your previous wife passed away. Is that correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.36,0:03:37.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.23,0:03:41.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Muramachi-han, you’re a samurai from Azuma, I believe?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.61,0:03:44.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are competing as a matter of business?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.62,0:03:45.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.57,0:03:52.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I recognize my weakness in this particular art,\Nand that it is closely tied to my own discipline.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.04,0:03:55.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I intend to marry Lady Ruri and devote myself to her craft.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.21,0:03:57.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.42,0:04:02.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As for myself, I am the great Oosawa\NRobou, a member of the imperial court.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.26,0:04:03.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the last of us…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.59,0:04:07.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.60,0:04:12.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my, I had heard that the fourth suitor was Jissonji-han.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.85,0:04:13.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.98,0:04:18.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am just a simple medicine seller.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.40,0:04:22.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why have you come here, then, Medicine Seller?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.15,0:04:25.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because there may already be{\alpha&HFF&} a Mononoke here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.20,0:04:26.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because there may already be a Mononoke here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.08,0:04:33.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my. That’s most interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.87,0:04:35.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Mononoke, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.58,0:04:38.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you were just a medicine seller.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.26,0:04:44.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or are you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.59,0:04:49.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, sirs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.22,0:04:52.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The contest is almost ready for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.73,0:04:55.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.44,0:05:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means Jissonji-han is late.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.40,0:05:06.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Such tardiness must mean he does\Nnot wish to marry Lady Ruri after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.33,0:05:10.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rar!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.69,0:05:41.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the heir to the Fue-no-Kouji School…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.66,0:05:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H—He’s not bowing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.54,0:06:00.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And why is he even here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.67,0:06:06.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is where Lady Ruri will decide\Nwhich of her suitors she will marry!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.42,0:06:10.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, no matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.89,0:06:21.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Being a medicine seller, do you ever\Nsell ingredients for incense, such as musk?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.90,0:06:23.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.61,0:06:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Well, you see, in this contest, we will\Nnot be hearing an animal-based scent,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.95,0:06:32.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but rather the fragrant wood of the agar.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.99,0:06:36.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The goal is to discern the slight differences in each piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.58,0:06:38.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Agar.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.37,0:06:44.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Its wood is so deeply permeated with aromatic\Nresin that it will sink when submerged in water, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.13,0:06:50.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, four contestants were scheduled to compete…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.63,0:06:57.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Madam, would you mind if this\Nman were to vie for your favor with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.39,0:07:01.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let it be so.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.94,0:07:03.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.28,0:07:12.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tonight’s contest will be Genjikou.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.24,0:07:15.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Genjikou.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.83,0:07:18.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s to be Genjikou, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.33,0:07:23.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don’t we make it simpler? Like, say, Taketori-no-Kou?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.79,0:07:25.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,U—Um, excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.79,0:07:33.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In Genjikou, you must hear five fragrances\Nin turn, then try to discern which are the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.93,0:07:38.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You use five blocks to signify\Nwhich of the fragrances is the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.93,0:07:41.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are fifty-two combinations in total.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.31,0:07:42.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,F—Fifty-two?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.31,0:07:47.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Each combination represents one of\Nfifty-two chapters of the Tale of Genji,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.07,0:07:53.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with the exceptions of the first chapter, Paulownia\NPavilion, and the final chapter, Floating Bridge of Dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.49,0:07:58.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For example, if these two and these two are the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.87,0:08:01.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it would represent Wood Pillar, as you can plainly see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.46,0:08:08.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so, if the second and fourth\Nscents are the same, you arrange them thus.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.88,0:08:12.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If five and three are also the same, thus.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.42,0:08:16.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If one and two are the only two that are the same, thus.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.47,0:08:18.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s all it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.22,0:08:22.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Each of the combinations simply has\Na different name and reason behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.48,0:08:26.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don’t have to know which\Ncorresponds to which in order to play.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.19,0:08:27.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I—I suppose…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.19,0:08:30.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh. I can tell you’re a {\i1}country{\i0} samurai.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.11,0:08:31.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.32,0:08:34.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Th—This was our hostess’s decision!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.45,0:08:43.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, Genjikou is usually played five times,\Nwith the most accurate contestant being the victor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.62,0:08:46.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This contest will last throughout the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.13,0:08:53.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The contest will be a single round,\Nafter which the victor will be decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.34,0:09:02.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, if there are two with the correct answer, there is no victor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.35,0:09:04.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, it’s a one-shot deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.14,0:09:06.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that all right with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.81,0:09:10.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let it be so.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.29,0:09:28.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The first scent is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.79,0:09:32.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.18,0:09:45.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My goodness!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.39,0:09:50.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a peaceful scent she chose to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.73,0:09:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It makes me feel like I’ve met a new friend; joy filling my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.03,0:09:59.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.66,0:10:09.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My goodness!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.92,0:10:14.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Such a nostalgic scent she chose to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.38,0:10:23.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It reminds me of a sunny day in my home, when\Nmy father scolded me for not attending to my studies.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.60,0:10:25.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.20,0:10:43.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The second scent is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.66,0:10:50.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The third scent is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.42,0:10:56.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is either Manaka or Manaban.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.97,0:11:01.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H—How are they different?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.68,0:11:04.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren’t they all the same?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.22,0:11:06.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’ve got no chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.10,0:11:10.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The fourth scent is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.69,0:11:14.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My goodness!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.77,0:11:16.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know this smell!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.61,0:11:18.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is… This is…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.91,0:11:24.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Horse dung?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.91,0:11:31.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Nue’s cry, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.16,0:11:33.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N—Nue?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.13,0:11:35.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it’s just the birds.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.67,0:11:43.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The fifth scent is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.76,0:11:48.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Decide how you will answer after this.{2half}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.14,0:11:52.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One and three are the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.44,0:11:57.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I believe four and the last one were, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.73,0:12:01.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinkyara? No, Sasora?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.03,0:12:06.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This one’s the same!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.83,0:12:13.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They’re all mocking me! They think I’m a bumpkin! A yokel!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.01,0:12:28.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is just overly difficult,\Nespecially when compared to Taketori-no-Kou.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.26,0:12:29.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Taketori!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.43,0:12:36.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was a chapter in the Tale of Genji, as\Nwell, wherein a lady was approached by four suitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.77,0:12:38.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,0)}Tamakazura!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.77,0:12:44.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did I not realize it before? Lady\NRuri is the same as Tamakazura herself!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.20,0:12:49.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamakazura!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.99,0:12:52.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is most likely Tamakazura.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.91,0:12:57.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, this man here must already know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.04,0:12:59.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can’t win with the same answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.54,0:13:01.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’ll have to take a chance here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.67,0:13:06.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Endless Summer!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.51,0:13:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do they find enjoyable about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.72,0:13:12.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some of them are different, they say?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.06,0:13:16.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ridiculous! They’re all the same, damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.77,0:13:19.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Writing Practice!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.90,0:13:27.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.83,0:13:34.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will record your answers. I ask that you retire.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.50,0:13:38.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jissonji-dono never came, did he?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.17,0:13:41.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind him!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.06,0:13:59.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I—It’s awfully cold tonight, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.90,0:14:03.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is a lavatory at the end of this hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.69,0:14:06.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O—O—Oh my. Very kind of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.32,0:14:08.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you’ll excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.36,0:14:10.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I—I think I will excuse myself, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.49,0:14:12.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, me as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.00,0:14:25.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where, I wonder, is the Toudaiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.31,0:14:38.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.64,0:14:43.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no. It’s nothing at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.99,0:14:51.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is{\alpha&HFF&} hesitating.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.20,0:14:52.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is hesitating.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.79,0:15:00.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is the Toudaiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.25,0:15:03.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps in that furthest room, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.44,0:15:27.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ack! What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.74,0:15:34.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ack! Medicine Man, what is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.49,0:15:38.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Mononoke has begun to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.70,0:15:40.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That again?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.83,0:15:45.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He’s talking to his sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.13,0:15:49.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You keep blabbering about Mononoke over\Nand over, but can you really use that sword to—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.55,0:15:50.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kill them. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.97,0:15:57.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to do so, I need its Form, Truth and Regret, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.99,0:16:11.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, I came too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.96,0:16:25.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M—My goodness!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.92,0:16:28.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jissonji-han!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.21,0:16:29.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s Jissonji-han!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.96,0:16:32.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you mean to tell us this was a Mononoke’s doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.47,0:16:38.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.55,0:17:14.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Ruri! Lady Ruri!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.96,0:17:14.05,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,My God! What happened to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.05,0:17:15.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.43,0:17:17.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did Jissonji-han kill Lady Ruri,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.30,0:17:21.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or did Lady Ruri kill Jissonji-han and then herself?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.43,0:17:23.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I can’t believe this!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.27,0:17:25.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone came in from outside, obviously!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.27,0:17:30.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When was Jissonji-han killed?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.98,0:17:38.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be he arrived before the rest of us,\Nand has been lying there dead all this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.03,0:17:39.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who was in this mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.03,0:17:42.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yourselves, Lady Ruri, the old woman…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.54,0:17:45.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There’s another. I saw a strange little girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.62,0:17:48.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you implying that a small girl killed two adults?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.75,0:17:50.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The T—Toudaiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.29,0:17:52.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is the Toudaiji safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.25,0:17:53.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,200)}Toudaiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.17,0:17:53.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Toudaiji!
