Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.68,0:18:01.51,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Toudaiji!{\alpha&HFF} Toudaiji! Toudaiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.51,0:18:02.26,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Toudaiji! Toudaiji!{\alpha&HFF} Toudaiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.26,0:18:03.39,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Toudaiji! Toudaiji! Toudaiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.92,0:17:56.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.57,0:18:16.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What’s this about the Toudaiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.78,0:18:23.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It isn’t here, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.66,0:18:26.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s kept in a safe place.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.33,0:18:33.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.17,0:18:36.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can’t see terribly well, so I cannot tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.55,0:18:42.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W—Well, that’s awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.43,0:18:44.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no! Jissonji-han’s—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.77,0:18:51.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there something in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.40,0:18:52.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must not open it!{}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.73,0:18:54.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must not go in!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.36,0:18:59.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There’s something terrible in\Nthere! Something unfit for a lady’s eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.32,0:19:02.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y—Yes! It’s incredibly raunchy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.70,0:19:04.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.66,0:19:06.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, be careful, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.04,0:19:12.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My heart almost gave way there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.96,0:19:16.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oosawa-dono, what are we to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.76,0:19:25.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One of us should have been able to gain the Toudaiji by\Nbecoming Lady Ruri’s husband and inheriting her school.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.68,0:19:29.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, we never saw the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.85,0:19:31.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This was the correct answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.77,0:19:33.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.06,0:19:35.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,200)}Broom Tree, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.52,0:19:37.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Broom Tree, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.98,0:19:40.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were all different scents, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.82,0:19:43.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was no victor, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.53,0:19:46.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Medicine Man, is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.99,0:19:52.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it was her,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.62,0:19:56.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I was obviously mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.46,0:19:58.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh—What is he talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.13,0:20:01.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, just talking to myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.17,0:20:06.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, what is this Toudaiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.64,0:20:10.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can’t possibly mean the temple, can you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.94,0:20:17.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With the lady dead, the Toudaiji has no rightful heir.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.61,0:20:21.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you say we decide who\Ngets it based on another Kumikou?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.99,0:20:24.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh—What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.11,0:20:26.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Ruri is dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.95,0:20:31.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only the four of us know, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.79,0:20:35.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. We’ll decide which of us is the\Nheir, and have a little wedding celebration.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.83,0:20:41.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We’ll say that she died after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.67,0:20:47.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the one who wins her hand will gain the Toudaiji.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.64,0:20:51.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.72,0:20:53.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will prepare the scents.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.60,0:20:55.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.15,0:20:58.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In return, tell me what the Toudaiji is!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.02,0:21:02.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this Toudaiji, which is wanted\Nso much more than Lady Ruri herself?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.03,0:21:03.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.32,0:21:07.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me ask you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.75,0:21:19.25,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}Without you, I just can’t smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.38,0:21:30.31,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}I walk this banal town,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.31,0:21:36.39,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}feeling such intense emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.94,0:21:42.78,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}I know that if I could treasure them and live on,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.86,0:21:52.08,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}I would need nothing else.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.74,0:22:00.25,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}The summer flowers that bloomed in the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.25,0:22:06.55,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}Come falling down, dancing in the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.63,0:22:09.89,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}I can barely recall the night sky
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.89,0:22:13.18,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}where they all came tumbling down,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.18,0:22:24.03,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}so what I can still recall is all the more precious.
